<p>Some modal verbs do not change in reported speech:</p>
<p>- Might</p>
<p>- Could</p>
<p>- Would</p>
<p>- Should</p>
<p>- Ought to</p>
<p>You do not need to change the tense if the reporting verb is in the present, or if the original statement was about something that is still true.</p>
<p><i>Ex: We explained that it is very difficult to sing like that.</i></p>
<p><b>Questions in reported speech</b></p>
<p>In order to report a question we have to do the following changes:</p>
<p>- Change the word order from question to statement.</p>
<p>- Make the same tense changes as for the statements</p>
<p>- Use the same question words</p>
<p>- Use a full stop and not a question mark.</p>
<p>- We do not use auxiliary verbs ‘do’, ‘does’ and ‘did’.</p>
<p>- Yes/ no questions use ‘if’ or ‘whether’</p>
<p><i>Ex: Where did you go yesterday? / He asked where I had gone the day before.</i></p>
<p><i>Have you finished your homework?/ He asked if I had finished my homework.</i></p>
<p><b>Changes in time and adverbs</b></p>
<p>- Today changes to that day/the same day</p>
<p>- Tomorrow changes to the next day/the following day</p>
<p>- Yesterday changes to the day before/the previous day</p>
<p>- Next week/month/year changes to the following week/month/year</p>
<p>- Last week/month/year changes to the previous week/month/year</p>
<p>- Now/just changes to then</p>
<p>- Ago changes to before</p>
<p>- Here changes to there</p>
<p>- This changes to that</p>
